did.unittitle: F. C. C. Boyd autograph collection

repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: Chiefly an autograph collection of approximately three hundred letters, two United States Navy Department letterbooks (1873-1876), photographs, drawings, and a small amount of F. C. C. Boyd's financial papers. Most of the items are American, although several are European, including one signed by Pope Urban VIII. Major topics covered by the colletion include numismatics, the theater, and the United States Navy.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The F.C.C. Boyd Autograph Collection contains approximately three hundred letters and other documents ranging in date from 1635 to 1934, arranged in alphabetical order. Although most of the papers are American in origin, several are signed by Europeans, including one document issued by Pope Urban VIII. Major topics covered by the collection include numismatics, the theater, and the United States Navy. Two Navy Department letterbooks (1873-1876) are included with the autograph letters.

Aside from autograph letters, the collection offers a miscellany of autographs cut from various documents, printed matter, photographs and drawings, and a visitors' book from the National Hobby Collectors Show Numismatic Exhibit of 1934-1935. There is, in addition, a small amount of financial papers pertaining to F.C.C. Boyd.
This autograph collection was donated to Yale University by F.C.C. Boyd in 1941.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Copyright status for collection materials is unknown, though much of the material in this collection is likely in the public domain.
